Name: Knock, knock
Description: I am the one who knocks - Hit the front door of the Huckster's House with the sledgehammer a few times to knock.

Name: Estate Agent
Description: Sell 20 houses.  Buy and sell 20 houses. Renovations not required.

Name: Senior Estate Agent
Description: "Sell 50 houses"  Buy and sell 50 houses. You don't have to renovate them for this achievement.

Name: Negotiator
Description: "Negotiate for at least 50,000 euro and win"  Note: you cannot earn this achievement if you do not have your currency set to "Euros". This can be done from the in-game Settings > General section at any time. The easiest way to earn this achievement is to max out your negotiation skill and sell the "Alone Home" house.

Name: Car mechanic
Description: "You'll need a car mechanic."  Earned by hitting a car in a garage with the hammer.

Name: Strongman
Description: "Do you even lift?"  Earned by picking up and moving a vehicle. It is possible to earn this achievement both while completing jobs and renovating houses.

Name: Millionaire
Description: "Earn the first million euro."  Available in other currency modes (adjusted from the in-game Settings > General section at any time). Fastest way to earn this is to purchase the House that is hiding something, break down the wall next to the breaker box, loot and sell what's in the secret room, sell house... repeat.

Name: Game Over
Description: "Finish the game."  Earned by selling EVERY house once. This requires you to move offices at least once in order to sell the first office.

Name: I'm a Belieber
Description: "Fashion is my armor against the realities of everyday life." Earned by selling a house to Gorgio Shanua.He prefers fashion over function. You must not have a kitchen, sell most of your furniture... a double bed and a 2 linen closets are a must.

Name: Geek
Description: "I'm not a genius, but I am smarter than you are."  Earned by selling a house to Chang Choi. The "Abandoned house" is best suited to his needs. You may have to make an open floor plan and add some children's toys to dissuade other potential buyers.

Name: Artistic Soul
Description: "Every child is an artist. The problem is how to remain an artist once we grow up."  Earned by selling a house to Veronica Liptson. Veronica's wants are simple: Art and plants. The easiest way to earn this achievement is to use the "Variable Woman's House", don't clean it, and add tons of art and plants.

Name: Mr. Mystery
Description: "Bra off, party on!"  Earned by selling a house to Jimmy Traitor. The "Home Admin-Legends" house has most of the amenities he wants. Remove the kitchen and turn it into a home theater. Don't forget the coffee table(s).

Name: Wall Street Shark
Description: "It's business. Leave your feelings at the door."  Earned by selling a house to Jack Tarinton. The "Hucksters House" is best set up for this. Clean it, make 2 bedrooms, 2 couches, and cheap furniture.

Name: Family Man
Description: "Family isn't just an important thing, it's everything."  Earned by selling a house to the Jonson Family. When working on this achievement, you must not have a complete kitchen or the Smoth couple will buy it EVERY TIME. The best way to do this is to use a bathroom sink instead of kitchen one and use the range tops instead of a full stove.

Name: Just Enough
Description: "Age is just a number. Live life fully, no matter how old you are.."  Earned by selling a house to the Jantart Family. The "Camping bungalow" home is best suited for their needs. Clean the home and install furnaces in every room. Furniture needs to be classic wooden or upholstered and retro looking. They also like rugs or carpet.

Name: Pro-creative
Description: "You know, when you're in love, you can't get any sleep… because of your kids screaming around the clock!"  Earned by selling a house to the Smoth family.

Name: The Tactical Prepper
Description: "Always be prepared for the unknown."  Earned by selling a house to Lonewolf37. The "Garage with a bunker" can be sold as is.

Name: Doomsday Prepper
Description: "Better to prep 10 years too early than 10 minutes too late!"  Earned by selling a house to Maria Kolkowsky. The "Old house with a bunker" is best suited for Maria's needs. It can be sold to her without renovations.

Name: The Survivalist
Description: "Remember: when disaster strikes, the time to prepare has passed."  Earned by selling a house to Ted Arrown. The "Garage with a bunker" house is best suited for his needs. Add 2 turbine generators and 2 bunk beds.

Name: Give it Some Fresh Air
Description: "Don't forget to take it out of the rain!."  Earned by taking your laptop outside from your "office" to your garden and using by pressing "E".

Name: Competitor
Description: "Look at my garden, it's amazing!"  Earned by competing in a Garden Competition. To do this, act as if you are selling the house and click "Submit garden for contest".

Name: Perfect Layout
Description: "Feel Shi… Fence Shi… Well, I tried."  Earned by getting 5 stars in "layout" during a Garden Competition. The "Garden After House Construction" home is best suited for this.

Name: According to the Rules
Description: "Blue flower, red thorns..."  Earned by getting 5 stars in "plant selection" during a Garden Competition.

Name: Fully Equipped
Description: "Didn't you forget about a few flowers between this sofa and carousel?"  Earned by getting 5 stars in "equipment" during a Garden Competition.

Name: Gardener
Description: "I feel this gardener aura inside of me."  Earned by maxing out skills for Garden Flipper DLC

Name: Vegan
Description: "Tell the meatatarians my last word is… Carrot…"  Earned by planting over 50 carrots.

Name: Let's Swim
Description: "Bath time?"  Fill a pond 15 times. A single or multiple ponds may be used.

Name: Whac A Mole
Description: "Your time has come, Mr. Mole..."  Earned by removing all the molehills present during one of the Garden Flipper DLC maps.

Name: Don Quixote
Description: "Is the hammer even real?"  Earned by installing a "Wooden Pedro Windmill", then hitting it with your hammer.

Name: Down to the Last Penny
Description: "Care to do something more with all that's left?"  Earned by using the entire budget on a job.

Name: Truly Open Space
Description: "Must have: lots of space"  Earned by tearing down all the walls during one of your jobs. This does not have to be completed in an HGTV home, It can be done on any property that has been purchased to flip.

Name: All the Possibilities!
Description: "On the other hand…"  Earned by re-doing an HGTV job and choosing the opposite choices you chose last time.

Name: Chimney Sweeper
Description: "Can you hear it?"  Earned by turning on the covered fireplace in the job "Uninvited Guests".

Name: Modern Solutions
Description: "Can't have a leak when there are no pipes!"  Earned in an HGTV job where you must bust a wall that has a connecting pipe behind it and sell the pipe instead of attempting to fix it.

Name: Time Warp
Description: "Let's do the time warp again!"  Earned by opening your portfolio and looking at your before and after photos.

Name: Oliver's Way
Description: "Now we're talking!"  Obtained by selecting Oliver's option three times in the same HGTV assignment.

Name: Greta's Touch
Description: "This place could use a woman's touch!"  Obtained by selecting Greta's option three times in the same HGTV assignment.

Name: Homer's House
Description: "I will not click on the map"  Earned by clicking on the house that looks like the Simpsons' home on the HGTV map.

Name: Renovator
Description: "Fix them all!"  Earned by completing all the jobs available on the HGTV map.

Name: Beach Please
Description: "Happiness is a day at the beach." (Secret) Earned by moving your office to beach front property.

Name: I hope there's no cellar
Description: "Now, who's in for a pool party?"  Place in-door pool first time.

Name: The furnisher
Description: "One man's trash is another man's treasure"  Fix a furniture first time.

Name: I fixed it!
Description: "All it takes is a good smack with a hammer"  Earned by 'fixing' the yacht wheel (second floor) by hitting it with the hammer

Name: Panorama
Description: "Take a picture of the city from the Cliff House"  Earned by taking a picture of the city, as stated, from the Cliff House. Best location to earn the achievement seems to be by the pool.

Name: I am rich
Description: "Purchase one of the houses from Luxury DLC"

Name: The Wi-Fi password, anyone?
Description: "The next step is to hire a butler"  Move your office to one of house of Luxury DLC.

Name: You are too creative!
Description: "If we allowed you to do this, the game would crash"  Attempt to sell the 'decision bubble' which is used to view the inspirations (the images that help you select what to use to fulfill the job).

Name: What's in the box?
Description: "Tons of cuteness to say the least!"  Complete the first Stowaway mission from Alice Finbar

Name: A journey full of fluffiness
Description: "Morgan is proud of you."  Complete all the jobs on the Pet DLC Map

Name: Welcome to Cozy Village
Description: "Hope you enjoy the countryside."  Move your office to one of the houses added with the Pet DLC

Name: Caretaker
Description: "Feels like the beginning of something special."  Buy a pet from Morgan's pet house

Name: Fresh, clean, and dry
Description: "Now your pup can get all dirty again."  Buy a special bath and bathe your pet in it

Name: Versatile caretaker
Description: "You're not gonna stop here, are you?"  Give shelter to three different animals in Morgan's pet house

Name: The floor is your canvas
Description: "Now, that's not a happy little accident."  Clean up feces with a mop

Name: Teamwork
Description: "A helping paw is never a bad thing, eh?"  Take your pet with you on a job using the pet interaction menu

Name: They grow up so fast...
Description: "It feels like we've met yesterday!"  Reach the adulthood of your pet

Name: Picture perfect
Description: "It's hard to get a good photo when they move around so quickly."  Take a picture of your pet using the tablet

Name: Old McDonald
Description: "Is there an animal you haven't got?"  Purchase at least one of each type of farm animal.

Name: Drone master
Description: "Making photos, watering, spraying… Everything on the fly!"  Get all three of the perks associated with the "High Tech Farmer" branch of the farming skill tree.

Name: The bigger the better
Description: "House extensions are just too much fun!"  Use the architecture tool to build a new building or house extension.

Name: Music to my ears
Description: "Your house, your rules, your radio."  Buy one of the new boomboxes added by the dlc and press E while selecting it to open the music folder.

Name: A long day in the countryside
Description: "Hard work pays off!"  Complete all the jobs on the Farm DLC Map

Name: Talented roofer
Description: "Show your true colors!"  Use the sell tool to change a roof. Can be earned during the "Mae Delicious" job.

Name: Free spirit
Description: "Finally, nothing limits your imagination!"  Buy one of the land parcel properties (Like A Painting, Spruce Hideout, and Country Idyll) and make it your office.

Name: Don't hold your horses
Description: "Ride like the wind!"  Jump with a horse over an obstacle

Name: Hardworking farmer
Description: "Your efforts have yielded a harvest."  Plant and harvest at least one of every crop.

Name: They're all in one basket
Description: "Still looking for a golden egg?"  Use the pantry tab on the tablet to take out 20 eggs and place them in the game world. Baskets of eggs can be combined and added to in order to get the achievement.

Name: Just don't get lost!
Description: "Fancy an afternoon snack with a Minotaur?"  Solve the corn maze in the "Grandpa's Surprise" job. The entrance is to the left of the house. The drone can be used to get a bird's eye view of the maze and objects can be placed to mark where you've been before.

Name: Appetite comes with eating
Description: "That was just the appetizer!"  Cook a meal in the universal cooker.

Name: Land in hot water
Description: "Keep your eyes down - there's no floor!"  Fall down the hole to the floor below in the Cloud-high Surprise job.

Name: The way to one's heart…
Description: "... is through the stomach. Would you like some more?"  Complete 5 Dine Out DLC jobs.

Name: Don't judge a restaurant by its sign
Description: "A great lure for customers"  Create a custom restaurant sign.

Name: The cherry on top
Description: "Everyone has the restaurant of their dreams."  Complete all 10 Dine Out DLC jobs.

Name: 5 Flipper stars
Description: "The art of cooking holds no secrets for me."  Make 5 recipes with the universal cooker.

Name: Why live on bread and water?
Flavours Hunter
Description: Unlock all the recipes for the universal cooker. These can be found in the Dine Out DLC jobs, and unlocked using perk points.

Name: Do it ASAP
Description: Complete order below 1min. Easily earned by quickly doing the first task - Ex-boyfriend Stole the Radiator from my house, 100% not required. (Note: this will reset the 100% bar on your tasks, so either get the "perfectionist" achievment first or go back and fully complete the order again.)

Name: Evolved (Silver)
Description: Defeat 100 enemies with Evolved Venom abilities

Name: Armed and Dangerous (Silver)
Description: Defeat 100 enemies with Spider Arm abilities

Name: Fully Loaded (Bronze)
Description: Purchase all of Spider-Man's Suit Tech upgrades

Name: Funky Wireless Protocols (Bronze)
Description: Solve the mystery of the Spider-Bots' origin

Name: Slack Line (Bronze)
Description: Stealth takedown 25 enemies in stealth from the Web Line

Name: Hang Ten (Bronze)
Description: Perform 30 Air Tricks in a row without touching the ground

Name: Home Run! (Bronze)
Description: Round the bases at the Big Apple Ballers Stadium

Name: Just Let Go (Bronze)
Description: As Miles, find the science trophy Miles and Phin won together

Name: You Know What to Do (Bronze)
Description: As Peter, visit Aunt May's grave

Name: Soar (Bronze)
Description: Using only your Web Wings, glide from the Financial District to Astoria (Wind Tunnels are okay!)

Name: Splat (Bronze)
Description: Attempt and fail a trick before "landing" on the ground

Name: Resourceful (Bronze)
Description: Collect a total of 10,000 Tech Parts

Name: Crimson Hour (Silver)
Description: Complete "It Was Meant for Me" (last mission in The Flame side story)

Name: Antidote (Bronze)
Description: Defeat a Symbiote that is under the effect of Anti-Venom status

Name: Once More, With Feeling (Platinum)
Description: Finish the main story in New Game+ mode

Name: Surge (Silver)
Description: Use Symbiote Abilities 25 times during Symbiote Surge

Name: Overdrive (Bronze)
Description: As Miles, use Reverse Flux to pull 6 or more enemies together simultaneously

Name: Let the light in!
Description: Turn on the light in the Tavern

Name: No pay, no food!
Description: A zombie wave has been repelled

Name: I should not drink at work
It's much more comfortable this way
Say no to alcohol!
Description: A drunken customer was chased away

Name: The wild boar population is under threat
Too smart to become a sausage
Wanted to fry the meat, but fried the house
You are a new dungeon master!
Oligarch! Why do you need so much?
Why do all potions smell so bad?
The smell doesn’t matter when the potion’s done right
Now it's not scary!
Description: All torches in the cave were fired

Name: Guys, calm down, it's just me, and there are many of you!
Ready for the school of mages!
Looks like I'm going to live forever
Description: Big MaxHP potion + Physical damage resist potion

Name: Is that you, Rapunzel?
Description: Jump to someone in the tower

Name: The wait wasn't that long
Description: Give the dish to the customer at the last moment (5 seconds)

Name: Theseus & Asterius - The Shield of Chaos
The Shield of Chaos - Breaching Rush
The Shield of Chaos - Charged Flight
The Shield of Chaos - Charged Shot
The Shield of Chaos - Dashing Flight
The Shield of Chaos - Dashing Wallop
The Shield of Chaos - Dread Flight
The Shield of Chaos - Empowering Flight
The Shield of Chaos - Explosive Return
The Shield of Chaos - Ferocious Guard
The Shield of Chaos - Minotaur Rush
The Shield of Chaos - Pulverizing Blow
The Shield of Chaos - Sudden Rush
Bat Cage, All-Seeing (can get info from this!)
Lyre, Splendid (can get info from this!)
A Bakers Dozen!
Description: Take Photos of 13 Gudetama - Use the Camera tool to take photos. The camera is collected after the side-quest Gudetama Snap, after reaching Friendship level 1 with Pochacco

Name: A New Home
Description: Open the Nature Preserve - Completed during the quest Open the Nature Preserve

Name: Aquatic Challenge
Description: Craft the Gold Reef Trophy - Complete all the Challenge Courses in Rainbow Reef to get the Crafting Plans for the Gold Reef Trophy.

Name: Baking Bliss
Description: Unlock 20 recipes at the Oven - The oven is located in Seaside Resort Plaza in Hello Kitty's Cafe. You can make a bunch of recipes using Flour.

Name: Behind the Waterfall
Description: The Hidden Meadow - Enter the Merry Meadow for the first time in the quest Curious Caverns

Name: Bog Champ
Description: Restore the Spooky Swamp - Completed during the quest Re-Haunt the Swamp

Name: Candy Connoisseur
Description: Unlock 10 Recipes at the Candy Cloud Station - The Candy Cloud Station is located in Cloud Island. Recipes are made using Candy Clouds as the main ingredient.

Name: Critter Master
Description: Catch 100 Critters - Use the Net tool to catch critters in each area. You can earn the Net during the quest Open the Nature Preserve.

Name: Definitely Haunted
Description: Restore the Haunted Mansion - Completed during the quest Re-Haunt the Swamp

Name: Delicious Desserts
Description: Unlock 16 Recipes at the Dessert Boat - The Dessert Boat is located within the Dessert Boat restaurant in Gemstone Mountain. Recipes are made using Cactus Cream.

Name: Dinosaurs Not Included
Description: Open the Resort Gate with Chococat - Completed during the quest Power Up the Gate

Name: Dozens Surely!
Description: Take Photos of 120 Gudetama - Use the Camera tool to take photos. Gudetama are scattered across all regions.

Name: Egg-cellent Chef
Description: Unlock 14 Recipes at the Egg Pan Station - The Egg Pan Station is crafted after completing the quest An Egg-cellent Pan. Recipes are made with eggs.

Name: Everyone is Welcome
Description: Have 20 Visitors at 5 Stars - Repair Visitor Cabins to have Visitors stay. Complete their Requests to boost their Star Rating.

Name: Everyone's Bestie
Description: Become Best Friends with 15 Characters - Increase Friendships by gifting gifts daily + completing quests with characters around the islands.

Name: Excellent Espresso
Description: Unlock 13 recipes at the Espresso Machine - The Espresso Machine is located in the Comedy Club within Rainbow Reef. Recipes are made with Candlenut.

Name: Floating Challenge
Description: Craft the Gold Cloud Trophy - Complete all the Challenge Courses in Cloud Island to get the Crafting Plans for the Gold Cloud Trophy.

Name: Floral Challenge
Description: Craft the Gold Meadow Trophy - Complete all the Challenge Courses in Merry Meadow to get the Crafting Plans for the Gold Meadow Trophy.

Name: Floral Pattern
Description: Obtain a patterned flower - Flowers are grown in Merry Meadow by planting seeds + waiting for the flower to bloom. To collect, approach + press the hand icon or E.

Name: Flower Collector
Description: Obtain 10 unique Flower Types - Flowers are grown in Merry Meadow by planting seeds + waiting for the flower to bloom. To collect, approach + press the hand icon or E.

Name: For the Love of Baking
Description: Cook 100 recipes - Prepare any recipe using the Oven in Hello Kitty's Cafe, 100 times.

Name: Friendship Forever
Description: Freed Big Challenges from his Icy Statis + Re-united TOPHAT with his Best Friend - Completed during the quest A Challenging Rescue

Name: Friendships Restored
Description: Reunite the Island Spirit with her Best Friends

Name: Happy Hattery
Description: Put a Hat on a Null - Interact with any Null + choose from any available hats in your Inventory to give it to them.

Name: Happy Landing!
Description: Another Happy Landing! - After completing the quest Happy Landings

Name: Haunted
Description: Fall through the floor of the Haunted Mansion - Fall through a trap door while completing the quest Re-Haunt the Swamp

Name: Hello Bestie!
Description: Become Best Friends with Hello Kitty - Reach Friendship level 25 with Hello Kitty

Name: Master Angler
Description: Catch 100 Fish - Use the Fishing Rod tool to catch fish in any region. The Fishing Rod is collected after completing the side-quest Keep It Reel when reaching Badtz-Maru Friendship level 3.

Name: Master of the Ruins
Description: Complete 20 Puzzle Rooms - Puzzle Rooms are temple-like structures spread through each region of the map. They usually contain Power Crystals or chests.

Name: Mermaids are Real
Description: Activate the Mermaidifier - Completed during the quest Comic Relief

Name: Nap Time
Description: Use a bed to change the time of day - Place a bed in your Cabin + interact with it to sleep + change the time of day.

Name: New Heights
Description: A Paradise in the Clouds - Enter Cloud Island for the first time in the quest Stargazing

Name: Open for Visits
Description: Unlock a Visitor Cabin - Visitor Cabins are unlocked by interacting with the signposts in the front of them + using Strawberry Crates for My Melody to repair them.

Name: Piza Perfection
Description: Unlock 11 recipes at the Pizza Oven - The Pizza Oven is located on Mount Hothead. Recipes are made with Dough.

Name: Rage Mode
Description: Ignited the Volcano with Retsuo's Rage - Completed during the quest Fire Up the Volcano

Name: Reef Revival
Description: Fully restore Rainbow Reef - Completed during the quest Reef Revival

Name: Regional Explorer
Description: Reaching every Region on Friendship Island - Friendship Island is made up of 5 regions -- Seaside Resort, Spooky Swamp, Rainbow Reef, Gemstone Mountain, + Mount Hothead. You'll venture to each within the main story quests.

Name: Rocky Challenge
Description: Craft the Gold Gemstone Trophy - Complete all the Challenge Courses in Gemstone Mountain to get the Crafting Plans for the Gold Gemstone Trophy.

Name: Soda Satisfaction
Description: Unlock 14 recipes at the Soda Fountain

Name: Superb Gift Giver
Description: Give 50 3-Star Gifts - Each character has different "Liked" items. Give Gifts that meet each one of their "Liked" items to make the Gift 3-Stars.

Name: Swampy Challenge
Description: Craft the Gold Swamp Trophy - Complete all the Challenge Courses in Spooky Swamp to get the Crafting Plans for the Gold Swamp Trophy.

Name: Swing Partners
Description: Reboot the Dance Hall band - Completed during the quest Bring Back the Swing

Name: Through Thick + Thin
Description: Have a character follow you to the lowest trench + tallest peak - To have someone follow you, ask them to help you out in dialogue with them or use the Phone "Call a Friend" app. The lowest trench is in Rainbow Reef area while diving + the tallest peak is the top of Icy Peak.

Name: Time for Milk
Description: Have Milk as a 5 Star Visitor

Name: Traveling Party
Description: Companion with one of your friends - Unlock the opportunity to companion with a character by increasing their Friendships. Then, ask them to help you out in dialogue with them or use the Phone "Call a Friend" app to make them your companion.

Name: Tropical Challenge
Description: Craft the Gold Seaside Trophy - Complete all the Challenge Courses in Seaside Resort to get the Crafting Plans for the Gold Seaside Trophy.

Name: True Gamer
Description: Play All the Mini Games Around Friendship Island - Mini Games are run by Nulls in each region of the map. Give them Game Tickets (collected around the ground of the map) to play the Mini Game.

Name: Vacation Hot Spot
Description: Repair twenty five visitor cabins - Approach Visitor Cabins + interact with the signposts out front to repair them with Strawberry Crates.

Name: Volcanic Challenge
Description: Craft the Gold Hothead Trophy - Complete all the Challenge Courses in Mount Hothead to get the Crafting Plans for the Gold Hothead Trophy.

Name: Badtz-maru - Level 9 - Gamer
Description: One free ticket use per day

Name: Big Challenges - Level 19 - Vacuum
Description: When foraging, items will be automatically picked up

Name: Chococat - Level 5 - Master Crafter
Description: Increases chance of getting extra item when crafting

Name: Hangyodon - Level 10 - Fish Friend
Description: Increases chance of rare fish appearing

Name: Hello Kitty - Level 2 - Sous Chef
Description: Increases chance of getting extra food item when cooking

Name: Keroppi - Level 9 - Critter Friend
Description: Helps keep critters from being startled

Name: My Melody - Level 4 - Big Smile
Description: Increases chance of getting an extra gift back when gifting to friends

Name: My Melody - Level 9 - Handy Helper
Description: Repairing visitor cabins costs 1 less strawberry crate

Name: My Sweet Piano - Level 13 - Master Interior Designer
Pekkle - Level 13 - Dance All Night
Description: Change time of day when talking to him

Name: Pompompurin - Level 12 - Slow + Steady
Description: Gives you 5 extra seconds to complete challenges

Name: Retsuko - Level 19 - Hot Stuff
Description: Swim in molten rock (Mount Hothead + Lava Caves)

Name: Tophat - Level 9 - Pickup Glitch
Description: Increases chance of getting 2 items when picking up an item

Name: Tuxedosam - Level 13 - Negotiator
Description: Increases chance to get extra item when shopping

Name: Usahana - Level 4 - Chef's Kiss
Description: Increases chance of getting an extra item when cooking with the Chef's station

Name: Wish Me Mell - Level 11 - Master Gardener
Description: Increases chance of getting a bonus seed when turning flowers into seed packets

Name: Wish Me Mell - Level 13 - Precision Play
Description: Reduces movement speed of the floating prizes in Crane Craze

Name: z 50th Anniversary Soda (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
z 50th Anniversary Frappe (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
z 50th Anniversary Latte (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
z 50th Anniversary Pizza Cookie #1 (Candy Cloud) (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
z 50th Anniversary Pizza Cookie #2 (Sugarkelp) (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
z 50th Anniversary Pizza Cookie #3 (Swampmallow) (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
z 50th Anniversary Cake (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
z 50th Anniversary Cheesecake (rare) (event Hello Kitty's 50th Anniversary)
Birthday Cake Shake (rare) (Happy Haven Days event)
z 50th Anniversary Boba (Hello Kitty 50th Anniversary event)
Seaside Resort - Grassy Hill Hustle
Description: On the hill west of Visitor Cabin #5

Name: Spooky Swamp - Ghost Tour Gallop
Description: North edge of the Ghost Tour Ride

Name: Spooky Swamp - Hedge Maze Havoc
Description: Eastern side of the Hedge Maze

Name: Spooky Swamp - Lily Pad Leap
Description: Northwest of Lilypad Lagoon at the top of the waterfall

Name: Spooky Swamp - Spooky Swamp Hop
Description: Northwest of the Witch's Hut at the top of the waterfall

Name: Spooky Swamp - Waterfall Falls
Description: East of Ghost Tour Ride, at the top of the waterfall

Name: Rainbow Reef - Coastal Trench Traverse
Description: North of the Comedy Club, East of the Kelp Maze

Name: Gemstone Mountain - Cactus Garden Chase
Description: West side of the Cactus Garden

Name: Gemstone Mountain - Island Cliff Shimmy
Description: Between Gemstone Mountain and Dune Lagoon

Name: Gemstone Mountain - Oasis Race
Description: Southeast of side of the Oasis

Name: Mount Hothead - Hothead Hot Foot
Description: Between Hot Springs and Red Hot Rampage

Name: Merry Meadow - Beanstalk Blastoff
Description: Southeast side of Merry Meadows Fields

Name: Merry Meadow - Cascade Caper
Description: Near Electric Introductions Puzzle Room door

Name: Merry Meadow - Garden Go Around
Description: North side of Merry Meadows Plaza

Name: Merry Meadow - Lumber Leaping
Description: Northwest side of Merry Meadows Overlook

Name: Cloud Island - Moonlight Slide
Description: Southwest of Cloud Island Critter Corral

Name: Cloud Island - Small Cloud Bop
Description: West side of Cloud Island Ponds

Name: Cloud Island - Water Wings Fly
Description: Northwest side of Cloud Island Ponds

Name: City Town - Around and About
Description: On rooftop on the west side of the Dumpster Alleyway

Name: City Town - City Swimming
Description: Northwestern side of City Center Plaza

Name: City Town - Sky Scraping
Description: In an alley on the western side of Town

Name: Seaside Resort - Blue Berryfly
Description: RARITY: Common /// TIME: All /// LOCATION: Near Resort Gate

Name: Seaside Resort - Castle Crab
Description: RARITY: Common /// TIME: Morning, Day, Evening /// LOCATION: Beaches

Name: Seaside Resort - Dragondarter
Description: RARITY: Uncommon /// TIME: Morning, Day /// LOCATION: Upper ponds

Name: Seaside Resort - Dunebug
Description: RARITY: Common /// TIME: Day, Evening, Night /// LOCATION: Hopscotch Islands, Moon Island

Name: Seaside Resort - Honey Bandit
Description: RARITY: Common /// TIME: Morning, Day, Evening /// LOCATION: Cozy Islands

Name: Seaside Resort - Scruffy Shortleg
Description: RARITY: Common /// TIME: Evening, Night /// LOCATION: Puzzle Rooms

Name: Seaside Resort - Sunslime
Description: RARITY: Common /// TIME: Morning, Evening, Night /// LOCATION: Beaches

Name: Spooky Swamp - Bush Friend
Description: RARITY: Uncommon /// TIME: Evening, Night /// LOCATION: Hedge Maze

Name: Spooky Swamp - Grassy Glowbuddy
Description: RARITY: Common /// TIME: All /// LOCATION: Near Ghost Tour Ride

Name: Spooky Swamp - Lily Frog
