Name: A Uniform for Richard's Son
LongDescription: #NAME?

Name: Blanche
LongDescription:
- Quest mentioned at the top for visibility, even if has to be done later in the game. WARNING: Do not kill any friendly Nevron for the rewards
- Complete every friendly Nevron side quest (marked as NEVRON in this list) and speak to Blanche to get your reward
- If any friendly Nevron is killed or every other Nevron side quest hasn't been completed, instead a boss fight with Blanche will trigger
- Untested if you can obtain the main rewards and then fight Blanche

Name: Jar Nevron
LongDescription:
- From Abandoned Expeditionary Camp: Acquire Resin; which is located behind some crates in the area to the left
- Return to the Jar Nevron and give the Resin
- Shoot at the tip of its lamp to light it
- Speak with them

Name: Demineur Nevron
LongDescription: - From Noco's Hut: Quest giver located at the crash site area of the Expedition 68's boat, go to the east, to an entrance similar to the Demineurs head\n- Aquire Intact Mine; from the quest giver, jump across the platforms and go to the right, jump across to another set of platforms and pick up the item\n- Return to the Demineur Nevron and give the Intact Mine

Name: Bourgeon Nevron
LongDescription:
- Quest giver located northwest to Flying Waters on the overworld map
- Acquire Burgeon Skin from defeating a Bourgeon boss (please refer to the Boss section of the checklist for locations)
- Give the item to the Nevron and wait (progress with the main story, another side quest or simply rest at a flag)
- Come back later and talk to them to claim the rewards, additionally it can be attacked to fight the "Grown Bourgeon" Boss

Name: Karatom The Gestral
LongDescription:
- Do before entering Act II. In the Gestral Village, past the Gestral Bazaar, talk to a kid named Karatom
- Acquire Mushroom; at Esquie's Nest. Pass through the guard, go right and jump down, go left from the Mime and pick up the item from the mushrooms
- Return to the Gestral Village and give the item to the quest giver
- Fight the Ultimate Sakapatate with Gustave and win

Name: Ono-Puncho Challenge
LongDescription: - Quest giver located on an isolated path in Gestral Village, talk to a big pink gestral.\n- He will ask you to do 9999 damage on one attack.\n- This can be achieved by: buffing Maelle with Gustave, then a second party member use an Energy Tint on Maelle. Maelle has to have the Medallum weapon and the Roulette and Marking Shots pictos. Additionally, she can have both the Burning Shots and Critical Burn Pictos/Lumina. On Maelle's turn, shoot Ono-Puncho until it gets marked (or marked+burnt) and the cast Percee. You can get lucky and do this in 2 tries or do 20 times and not get it.

Name: Help Alexaundro
LongDescription: - Quest giver located near Karatom, talk to them to start the quest\n- Reach the kid in the column: head north toward the Arena, take an immediate right to march down the southeastern path, then take a slight left at the end of the eastern passage, use the rope to climb onto an overhead platform, take a few steps west and use the grapple point to clear the gap head north and use the handholds on the wall, mantle over the short wall, and with a running start, leap onto the column to reach Alexsoundro's patate\n- Talk to the kid and then talk to Alexaundro

Name: The Fountain (Nevron)
LongDescription: - Quest giver located west to the Ancient Sanctuary (needed for Blanche quest)\n- Interact with the fountain and pay 5k, 10k, 25k and 50k chroma (total of 90k chroma)\n- Talk to the nevron to acquire the rewards

Name: Hexga Nevron
LongDescription:
- Quest giver located in the Old Farm, outside the Tide Caverns, talk to them and answer "How did this happen?" then probe more questions
- Aquire 3 Rock Crystals from the Tide Cavern. Two are inside glowing rocks and the last one is obtained by defeating the Rocher Boss in the right section
- Return where the Nevron was and give the Rock Crystals
- Pick the rewards from where it was sitting

Name: Trobadour Nevron
LongDescription:
- Quest giver located northeast of the Forgotten Battlefield on the overworld map
- Talk to them and accept their challenges (3)
- Parry or dodge the red orbs, get hit by the green orbs
- Talk again to claim the rewards

Name: Grandis
LongDescription:
- Quest giver located northeast of Monoco's Station on the overworld map
- Talk to them and accept their quest
- Use the Paint Break ability to break the ice
- Talk again to claim the rewards

Name: Portier Nevron
LongDescription: #NAME?

Name: Danseuse Teacher (Nevron)
LongDescription: #NAME?

Name: Chalier Nevron
LongDescription: #NAME?

Name: Fading Spirit
LongDescription: #NAME?

Name: Stone Wave Cliffs - Chromatic Hexga (Stone Wave Cliffs Cave)
The Monolith - Chromatic Clair Obscur (The Monolith)
The Continent - Chromatic Reaper Cultist (The Continent)
The Continent - Chromatic Boucheclier (Isle of the Eyes)
The Continent - Chromatic Catapult Sakapatate (Dark Gestral Arena)
The Continent - Chromatic Ranger Sakapatate (Dark Gestral Arena)
The Continent - Chromatic Robust Sakapatate (Dark Gestral Arena)
The Continent - Chromatic Cruler (Endless Night Sanctuary)
The Continent - Chromatic Gold Chevaliere (Crimson Forest)
Dodger
Description: Gain 1 AP after Perfect Dodge. Once per turn.
LongDescription: Spring Meadows (Meadows Corridor)\nDefeat the Portier after Lune joins the party.

Name: Critical Burn
Description: 25% increased Critical Chance on Burning Enemies
LongDescription: Spring Meadows (Meadows Corridor)\nAfter getting Lanceram, look for a path on the right that leads to a small cave.

Name: Augmented Attack
LongDescription: Spring Meadows (Meadows Corridor)\nDefeat the Chromatic Lancelier after learning about flying enemies.

Name: Burning Shots
Description: 20% Chance to burn on free Aim Shot
LongDescription: Spring Meadows (Abandoned Expeditioner)\nFrom the campsite, go through the cave path until you're outside, and then head left towards the cliff.

Name: Dead Energy II
LongDescription: Spring Meadows (Abandoned Expeditioner)\nFrom the campsite, go through the cave path. When you're outside, turn right and follow the path.

Name: Cleansing Tint
Description: Healing Tints also remove all Status Effects from the target
LongDescription: Spring Meadows (The Indigo Tree)\nDefeat Eveque, the boss of the area, to get this Pictos.

Name: Empowering Attack
Description: Gain Powerful for 1 turn on Base Attack
LongDescription: Spring Meadows (The Indigo Tree)\nInstead of leaving Spring Meadows after the Eveque fight, turn around and follow the path on the right.

Name: SOS Shell
Description: Apply Shell when falling below 50% Health
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Before Any Flag)\nImmediately upon loading the map, enter the path to the left of the anchor. The Pictos is on the ground at the end of the path.

Name: Marking Shots
Description: 20% Chance to apply Mark on Free Aim shot
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Before Any Flag)\nFollow the path beyond the Paint Cage to reach a fork that is marked with several lanterns on the ground. Head left at the fork and defeat the two enemies at the end of the path. The Pictos is on the ground just past those enemies.

Name: Exposing Attack
Description: Base Attack applies Defenceless for 1 turn
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Noco's Hut)\nAfter Gustave and Lune extract Maelle from the Manor, speak with the Gestral Merchant who appears in front of the hut. Fight and defeat that merchant to add this Pictos to their wares.

Name: Staggering Attack
Description: 50% Increased Break Damage on Base Attack
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Coral Cave)\nPass the Flag and immediately look to the right to find this Pictos on the ground.

Name: Rewarding Mark
Description: +2 AP on dealing damage to a Marked target. Once per turn.
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Coral Cave)\n(1) Players will encounter a mass from which several lanterns extend just past the Expedition Flag. After passing that mass, players should look for a short ramp on their left, which leads to an alcove with this Pictos. (2) Buy from Merchant for 53,880 Chroma from Sacred River.

Name: Augmented Counter I
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Coral Cave)\nPlayers can now climb the aforementioned two-handhold wall and follow the path forward. Before reaching the buildings on this path, players should enter a small corridor on their right and fight the Bourgeon that they encounter to obtain the Pictos, weapon, and quest item.

Name: Energising Break
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Lumieran Street)\nThis Pictos is on the ground just past the Chromatic Troubadour.

Name: Versatile
Description: After a Free Aim hit, base attack damage is increased by 50% for 1 turn.
LongDescription: Flying Waters (Lumieran Street)\nPlayers who head straight forward from the Flag will find that there are two buildings emerging from the ground. Players should get on top of those buildings and then use their grappling hooks to reach the buildings on the side of the area. Players should then go right and grab this Pictos from the ground.

Name: Energising Jump
LongDescription: Ancient Sanctuary (Entrance)\nFind this Pictos on the ground to the left of the illuminated spot that was used to trap the local Petank.

Name: Burning Mark
Description: Apply Burn on hitting a Marked enemy
LongDescription: Ancient Sanctuary (Entrance)\nPlayers should follow the stream in the area with the Petank to reach a wall with handholds, which they can shimmy across. This action will lead players to a small area with this Pictos.

Name: Energising Start II
LongDescription: Ancient Sanctuary (Sanctuary Maze)\nAfter passing the Sanctuary Maze Expedition Flag, players should go right at the fork and look for a small alcove on their right. There is a low gap in this alcove through which players can crawl, and they should go right when they emerge. Players should then make their way to the far end of the area and use the two handholds on the left to climb a small wall. There is a path at the top that leads directly to this Pictos.

Name: Attack Lifesteal
LongDescription: Ancient Sanctuary (Sanctuary Maze)\nPlayers should now descend the handholds that they used to reach the Energising Start II Pictos and enter the tunnel that is ahead. This tunnel leads to a Catapult Sakapatate, who is guarding this Pictos in a small alcove.

Name: Piercing Shot
Description: 25% increased Free Aim damage. Free Aim shots ignore Shields
LongDescription: Ancient Sanctuary (Sanctuary Maze)\nIn the area just before the area with the blue statues, use paint break to destroy a root. Head forward to the Gestral Totem expedition flag. Jump into the water and follow it into an alcove with the Pictos.

Name: Breaker
LongDescription: Ancient Sanctuary (Giant Bell Alley)\nPlayers will encounter the Ultimate Sakapatate, the map's final boss, not long after passing the Giant Bell Alley Expedition Flag, and they will receive this Pictos upon besting the foe in combat.

Name: Stun Boost
LongDescription: Ancient Sanctuary (Giant Bell Alley)\nThere is a tunnel through which players can crawl next to the Energy Tint Shard, and the path that is beyond that tunnel leads directly to this Pictos.

Name: Critical Moment
Description: 50% increased Critical Chance if Health is below 30%.
LongDescription: Gestral Village\nBuy from the Bazaar

Name: Roulette
Description: Every hit has a 50% chance to deal either 50% or 200% of its damage
LongDescription: Gestral Village\nSpeak to the Gambler

Name: Healing Mark
Description: Recover 25% Health on hitting a Marked enemy. Once per turn.
LongDescription: Gestral Village\nIn the Bazaar, enter the alcove to trigger a duel with a black market Gestral. Defeat to unlock in shop.

Name: Last Stand Critical
LongDescription: Hidden Gestral Arena\nBeat Matthieu

Name: Accelerating Last Stand
LongDescription: Hidden Gestral Arena\nBeat Bertrand

Name: Protecting Last Stand
LongDescription: Hidden Gestral Arena\nBeat Dominique

Name: Solo Fighter
Description: Deal 50% more damage if fighting alone.
LongDescription: Hidden Gestral Arena\nBeat Julien

Name: Empowering Last Stand
LongDescription: Hidden Gestral Arena\nBeat all opponents

Name: Augmented Aim
LongDescription: Gestral Village\nSpeak with Merchant in Bazaar after completing Forgotten Battlefield.

Name: Augmented First Strike
Description: 50% Increased damage on the first hit. Once per battle
LongDescription: Esquie's Nest\nDefeat Francois.

Name: Energising Start III
LongDescription: Esquie's Nest\nLeave the cave after Esquie makes the path for you, and the Pictos will be outside in the front entrance.

Name: Defensive Mode
Description: On receiving damage, consume 1 AP to take 30% less damage, if possible.
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs\nEnter through the portal on the beach. Look forward and to the left.

Name: Confident
Description: Take 50% less damage, but can't be healed
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Rest Point)\nDefeat the big rock monster 'Hexga' on the path after the entrance rest point.

Name: Breaking Counter
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Rest Point)\nLook to the left of the rock monster to find an old ship. Inside the ship is the Pictos

Name: Energising Pain
Description: No longer gain AP on Parry. +1 AP on getting hit
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Rest Point)\nAfter beating the rock monster, Hexga, continue forward to find some more monsters in the next area. Beat the enemy on the left side of the area to find the Pictos.

Name: First Strike
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Paintress Shrine)\nBefore using the grappling point that leads to the Paintress Shrine rest area, hop on the platforms to the right to find a side area with an enemy and a secret Pictos.

Name: SOS Power
Description: Apply Powerful when falling below 50% health
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Paintress Shrine)\nWhen a monster jumps out at you, hug the right wall to find a slope leading to the Pictos.

Name: Breaking Shots
Description: 50% increased Break damage with Free Aim shots
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Tide Caverns)\nWhen you're looking for the three rock crystals in a cave, you need to jump across some tall platforms with careful timing.

Name: Perilous Parry
Description: +1 AP on Parry, but damage received is doubled.
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Tide Caverns)\nDefeat the enemy on the bottom level of the caverns.

Name: Auto Shell
Description: Apply Shell for 3 turns on battle start.
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Tide Caverns)\nGive three crystals to Hexga.

Name: Healing Tint Energy
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs - Flooded Buildings\nGrapple back across, return to the bottom of the building, and use the grapple point to the left to cross the gap. Continue along the path to encounter two Nevrons. The Healing Tint Energy Pictos is on the ground just past those enemies.

Name: Enfeebling Mark
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs - Flooded Buildings\nDescend through the structure and follow the path to enter yet another building. Climb to the top and look left upon exiting the building to find a grapple point that can be used to reach an area with the Enfeebling Mark Pictos.

Name: At Death's Door
Description: Deal 50% more damage if health is below 10%
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs (Basalt Waves)\nDefeat the Lampmaster boss

Name: Dead Energy I
LongDescription: The Continent\nFound on the Continent, in front of the entrance to Dark Shores, about 100 feet away is a cluster of crates you can break apart, containing the Picto.

Name: Healing Parry
LongDescription: The Continent\nThere is a Bourgeon between Esquie's Nest and Stone Wave Cliffs. There is a Lost Gestral just past it, and this Pictos is in a camp nearby.

Name: Energising Start I
LongDescription: The Continent\nBeach north of Gestral Village

Name: Protecting Heal
Description: Healing an ally also applies Shell for a turn
LongDescription: Esoteric Ruins/Continent (Near Old Lumiere Entrance)\nFind the Wood Boards and give it to the spirit by the entrance

Name: Accelerating Heal
Description: Healing an ally also applies Rush for 1 turn
LongDescription: The Continent\nOn the first Painting Workshop isle. Walk to the opposite side past the monsters.

Name: Shared Care
Description: When healing an ally, also Heal self for 50% of that value
LongDescription: The Continent\nOn the island with the portal into White Tree.

Name: Energising Heal
Description: On Healing an ally, also give 2 AP
LongDescription: The Continent\nSmall beach north of the island with the portal into White Tree.

Name: Empowering Dodge
Description: 5% increased damage for each consecutive successful dodge. Can stack up to 10 times.
LongDescription: The Continent\nWalk a little north of Endless Night Sanctuary to find this on the ground.

Name: Fueling Break
Description: Breaking a target doubles its burn amount
LongDescription: The Continent\n(1) Near the entrance to The Carousel. (2) Complete Stage 7, Trial 3 of the Endless Tower

Name: Charging Tint
Description: +5% of a Gradient Charge on using an item.
LongDescription: The Continent\nIn a camp next to the merchant on small beach southeast of Gestral Beach (NW). Surrounded by enemies.

Name: Burning Death
Description: Apply 3 Burn to all enemies on Death
LongDescription: The Continent\nBeat Bourgeon that is near Merchant NW of Gestral Beach (NW).

Name: Breaking Burn
Description: 25% increased Break damage on Burning enemies
LongDescription: The Continent\nPast Burning Death Bourgeon.

Name: Cheater
Description: Always play twice in a row
LongDescription: The Continent\nDefeat Sprong. It's a huge enemy walking in the water next to Blades' Graveyard/Crimson Forest.

Name: Longer Burn
LongDescription: The Continent\nBeat the Chromatic Aberration on floating island between Dark Shores and The Fountain.

Name: Breaking Death
Description: Fully charge enemy's Break Bar on death
LongDescription: The Continent\nDefeat the Eveque east of Stone Wave Cliffs Cave.

Name: Breaking Slow
Description: 25% increased Break damage against Slowed enemies.
LongDescription: The Continent\nPaint Break a root southeast of Abbest Cave in the area filled with statues.

Name: Energising Shell
LongDescription: The Continent\nThe Picto can be found in a paint spike in the area of the Chromatic Petank to the east of The Meadows on the world map (accessible via Esquie flight).

Name: Energising Gradient
LongDescription: The Continent\nBeat the Frost Eveque northeast of Forgotten Battlefield exit.

Name: Warming Up
Description: 5% increased damage per turn. Can stack up to 5 times.
LongDescription: The Continent\nBeat the Grosse Tete in front of Coastal Cave (northeast of Forgotten Battlefield)

Name: Energy Master
Description: Every AP gain is increased by 1.
LongDescription: The Continent\nDefeat the Serpenphare (flying dragon boss).

Name: Longer Rush
Description: On applying Rush, its duration is increased by 2.
LongDescription: The Continent\nLook east of Monoco's Station/south of Frozen Hearts to find an ice monster near a broken camp.

Name: Anti-Stun
LongDescription: The Continent\nBeat the Chromatic Petank in the field southeast of Forgotten Battlefield/East of Gestral Village.

Name: Longer Shell
Description: On applying Shell, its duration is increased by 2
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Main Gate)\nDefeat the first wild enemy after entering the gates of Forgotten Battlefield.

Name: Sweet Kill
Description: Recover 50% health on killing an enemy
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Main Gate)\nAfter entering the main area, enter a side area to the left that leads you to some items, including the Pictos.

Name: Energising Start IV
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Main Gate)\nRight side of the big open area. In the trenches.

Name: Energising Death
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Fort Ruins)\nFrom the Flag, use the footholds, follow the path until you see a staircase to the right. Defeat the enemy patrol and look to the left to find a hidden item.

Name: Energising Parry
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Battlefield)\nWhen you see the Faded Woman near the flag, turn to the right and go through the hall, and then take the second right to find a special enemy called Chromatic Luster. It'll drop the Pictos.

Name: Empowering Tint
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Battlefield)\n(1) Same area as above. Turn right at the woman, take the first right to find a magic rope. (2) Complete Stage 8, Trial 3 of Endless Tower

Name: Inverted Affinity
Description: Apply Inverted on self for three turns at battle start. 50 % increased damage while inverted.
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Ancient Bridge)\nWhen you pick up the Expedition 57 journal, look nearby to find stairs leading to a rope. You'll find the trader Kasumi.

Name: Combo Attack I
Description: Base attack has one extra hit
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Ancient Bridge)\nFight the boss after passing this flag.

Name: Revive Tint Energy
LongDescription: Forgotten Battlefield (Ancient Bridge)\nFrom the flag, cross the bridge using the grapple, turn right to enter a new woodsy area to find the Pictos in the middle.

Name: Healing Counter
LongDescription: Old Lumiere (Entrance)\nBuy from Merchant near Entrance rest point - 20,400 Chroma.

Name: Longer Powerful
Description: On applying Powerful, its duration is increased by 2
LongDescription: Old Lumiere (Entrance)\nBuy from Merchant near Entrance rest point - 20,400 Chroma.

Name: Time Tint
LongDescription: Old Lumiere (Right Street)\nPass the grappling point, you'll eventually have to jump over a gap before reaching the next area, but if you drop down a ledge to the right, you'll find this Pictos. If you've reached the faded man, you've gone too far.

Name: Auto Rush
Description: Apply Rush for three turns on battle start
LongDescription: Old Lumiere (Right Street)\nWhen Maelle and Verso split, you're gonna use a grapple point to cross a broken bridge. Turn left after walking forward a bit to find three enemies huddled around the Pictos.

Name: Healing Death
Description: On death, the rest of the Expedition recovers all Health.
LongDescription: Old Lumiere (Manor Gardens)\nAfter Renoir is defeated, follow the path beyond the Paint Cage to access a section that is filled with grapple points, threads, and handholds. After traversing that section, descend the slope and defeat the Nevron at the bottom to obtain the Perilous Parry Pictos. The Healing Death Pictos is on the ground next to that Nevron.

Name: Revive Paradox
LongDescription: Old Lumiere (Train Station Ruins)\nAfter beating Renoir, return to the Entrance expedition flag and follow the critical path to reach a ledge where two gold threads can be activated. Head right at the ledge to reach the Train Station Ruins expedition flag, and continue forward, descending a gold thread when necessary, to reach the Chromatic Danseuse.

Name: Healing Share
Description: Revive 15% of all Heals affecting other characters
LongDescription: Visages (Plazza)\nBuy from Merchant nearby for 19,200 Chroma.

Name: Confident Fighter
Description: 30% increased damage, but can't be healed
LongDescription: Visages (Joy Vale)\nFrom the flag, pass the first group of dancing monsters, keep heading right until you see a big moving face with closed eyes. Head up the hill to the right to find an enemy near the pictos.

Name: Double Burn
Description: On applying a Burn stack, apply a second one
LongDescription: Visages (Anger Vale)\nFrom the Flag, head to the right towards the big face. Look to the right to find a little cave. Walk inside and then towards the left to find some enemies standing near the Pictos.

Name: Powered Attack
Description: On every damage dealt, try to consume 1 AP. If successful, increase damage by 20%
LongDescription: Visages (Anger Vale)\nFrom the Flag, head right towards the big face, but head left into a corridor that leads to a magic rope and a Pictos.

Name: Augmented Counter II
LongDescription: Visages (Anger Vale)\nFrom the flag, head straight and then right to find a hidden area leading to Chromatic Ramasseur. Defeat it to get the Pictos.

Name: Glass Canon
Description: Deal 25% more damage, but take 25% more damage
LongDescription: Visages (Anger Vale)\nRight next to where the Chromatic Ramasseur is (same as above)

Name: Immaculate
Description: 30% increased damage until a hit is received
LongDescription: Visages (Plazza)\nBeat the Axon boss (Visages / Mask Keeper)

Name: Shield Affinity
Description: 30% increased damage while having Shields, but receiving any damage always removes all shields.
LongDescription: Sirene (Dancing Classes)\nGo forward on the main path up the stairs, and then go inside the room to the left to find stairs. Go down to find a magic rope. Use the grapple to reach a paint cage. Destroy its parts to get the Pictos.

Name: Effective Heal
LongDescription: Sirene (Dancing Classes)\nGo forward on the main path up the stairs, and then go inside the room to the left to find stairs. Go down to find a magic rope. Use the grapple to reach a paint cage. Use the magic platform to reach a new area and then turn right to find the Pictos behind the Chromatic Greatsword Cultist.

Name: Greater Shell
LongDescription: Sirene (Dancing Classes)\nWhen you get off the moving platform to land in the area where the Chromatic enemy is, go to the opposite end to find this Pictos and some handholds.

Name: Powerful on Shell
LongDescription: Sirene (Dancing Classes)\nWhen you get to the room with the large statue in the middle, head to the right to enter a multi tiered room that looks like the inside of an organ. Head to the bottom of this area to find the Benisseur. Defeat it to get the pictos.

Name: Auto Regen
Description: Apply Regen for three more turns on battle start
LongDescription: Sirene (Dancing Classes)\nWhen you get to the room with the large statue in the middle, head to the right to enter a multi-tiered room that looks like the inside of an organ. Head to the bottom of this area.

Name: Protecting Death
LongDescription: Sirene (Dancing Classes)\nGo past the door to the Manor, and then take a right before the next grapple point.

Name: Anti-Charm
LongDescription: Sirene (Sewing Atelier)\nDefeat the Tisseur (large optional weaver boss)

Name: Healing Fire
Description: Recover 25% of health when attacking a Burning foe. Once a turn
LongDescription: Sirene (Crumbling Path)\nHead to the right from the flag to find a magic rope. Head down, use the grapple point, and follow the trail to find this Pictos.

Name: Double Mark
Description: Mark requires 1 more hit to be removed
LongDescription: Sirene (Crumbling Path)\nFrom the flag, head to the area on the left to find handholds. Use them to reach a magic rope. Follow the path to find a Merchant at the end of it.

Name: Energising Attack II
LongDescription: Sirene (Crumbling Path)\nSame as above

Name: Greater Powerful
LongDescription: Sirene (Crumbling Path)\nSame as above

Name: Energising Turn
LongDescription: Sirene\nBeat the boss, Sirene, at the end of the map.

Name: Energising Cleanse
Description: Dispel the first negative Status Effect received and gain 2 AP.
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Meadows)\nHead into the watery area after the second black and white scene with the Paintress. Look on the path to the left to find the merchant. Fight him to buy the Pictos for 40,800 Chroma.

Name: Stay Marked
Description: 50% chance to apply Mark when attacking a Marked enemy
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Waters)\nGo straight from the flag to find a little hidden path leading to the Chromatic Bourgeon. The Pictos is right behind it.

Name: Weakness Gain
Description: +1 AP on hitting an enemy's weakness once per turn
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Cliffs)\nWhen you go past the windmill and head on the main path, you'll end up in an area with a Hexga. Look on the right side to find this Pictos.

Name: Random Defense
Description: Damage taken is randomly multiplied by a value between 50% and 200%
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Cliffs)\nTurn around, leave the cave, and head to the right to find a secluded area with a Paint Cage. Need Paint Break to reveal one of its locks.

Name: Empowering Parry
Description: Each successful parry increases damage by 5% until end of the following turn. Taking damage removes this buff.
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Hearts)\nWhen the path splits for the first time, head left past a huge rock monster to find a grapple point leading to a Paint Cage.

Name: Greater Defenceless
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Hearts)\nWhen the path splits for the first time, turn left and then look to the right to find some handholds on the wall leading to a Merchant.

Name: Enfeebling Attack
Description: Base Attack applies powerless for 1 turn
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Hearts)\nCross the bridge beyond the Tainted Hearts expedition flag and immediately go left to enter an area with Gargant, a large Nevron. There are handholds on the wall to the right of that foe, and they lead to a merchant that sells a variety of items. The Enfeebling Attack Pictos is on the ground just past the merchant, next to a wrecked train.

Name: Breaking Attack
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tainted Lumiere)\nWhen you pass the big tree into a new area, immediately turn left and grapple onto the platform on the other side to fight some enemies.

Name: Second Chance
Description: Revive with 100% Health. Once per battle
LongDescription: Inside the Monolith (Tower Peak)\nDefeat Renoir

Name: Combo Attack II
LongDescription: Monolith Peak (Entrance)\nAfter beating the Paintress, return to the arena in which you fought her to encounter Chromatic Clair Obscur. Beat the Nevron to obtain the Combo Attack II Pictos.

Name: Painted Power
LongDescription: Monolith Peak\nDefeat the Paintress.

Name: Shortcut
Description: Immediately play when falling below 30% health. Once per battle
LongDescription: Lumiere (Harbour)\nFight the Abberation near the first big horse statue.

Name: Energising Powerful
LongDescription: Lumiere (Harbour)\nWhen you need to use the magic rope at the end of the initial path, ignore the grapple point to the left and instead head on the path to the right to lead you to the Pictos.

Name: Charging Stun
Description: +5% of a Gradient Charge on hitting a Stunned enemy
LongDescription: Lumiere (Shattered Alley)\nFrom the flag, turn around to see the Pictos near the large tree.

Name: Augmented Counter III
LongDescription: Lumiere (Shattered Alley)\nContinue the path until you spot a large creature with a light on its head. Defeat the Chromatic Echassier.

Name: Healing Stun
Description: Recover 5% Health on hitting a Stunned target
LongDescription: Lumiere (Opera House)\nFollow the path, use two grapple points, head on the left path, and keep an eye on the right wall to find this one. (You can find a dupe on the opposite side.)

Name: Full Strength
LongDescription: Lumiere (Lumiere's Gardens)\nBuy from Merchant after fighting him. Turn around and the merchant will be to the left. 53,200 Chroma.

Name: Gradient Fighter
LongDescription: Lumiere (Lumiere's Gardens)\nWhen you start walking the main path after the flag, turn on the second set of staircases to the left to find a Pictos by some enemies.

Name: Faster Than Strong
Description: Always play twice in a row, but deal 50% less damage
LongDescription: Lumiere (Lumiere's Gardens)\nFight Creation at the end of the garden path to get this.

Name: Draining Cleanse
Description: Consume 1 AP to prevent Status Effects application, if possible.
LongDescription: The Reacher (Entrance)\nAfter you grapple and use a magic rope, look right to see the Pictos behind enemies.

Name: Sniper
Description: First Free Aim shot each turn deals 200% increased damage and can Break
LongDescription: The Reacher (Mountain)\nFight the first group of monsters after the flag.

Name: Charging Counter
Description: +10% of a Gradient Charge on Counterattack.
LongDescription: The Reacher (Mountain)\nBefore the second hot air balloon ride, look to the left to find handholds leading to a side area. You'll find the Pictos at the end of it.

Name: Charging Attack
Description: +15% of a Gradient Charge on Base Attack
LongDescription: The Reacher (Mountain)\nBefore the second hot air balloon ride, look to the left to find handholds leading to a side area. You'll find the Pictos at the end of it.

Name: Protecting Tint
LongDescription: The Reacher (Foggy Area)\nCross the second wooden bridge and then turn right.

Name: Anti-Blight
LongDescription: The Reacher (Foggy Area)\nHead to the path on the left to find a hot air balloon ride, and speak to the nearby Merchant. 67,350 Chroma.

Name: Exposing Break
LongDescription: The Reacher (Foggy Area)\nHead to the path on the left to find a hot air balloon ride, and speak to the nearby Merchant. 53,880 Chroma.

Name: Charging Weakness
Description: 15% of a Gradient Charge on hitting a Weakness. Once per turn.
LongDescription: The Reacher (Foggy Area)\nHead to the path on the left to find a hot air balloon ride, and speak to the nearby Merchant. 53,880 Chroma.

Name: Tainted
Description: 15% Increased damage for each Status Effect on self
LongDescription: The Reacher (Foggy Area)\nHead to the path on the left to find a hot air balloon ride, and speak to the nearby Merchant. 49,391 Chroma.

Name: Healing Boon
Description: Heal 15% HP on applying a buff
LongDescription: The Reacher (Foggy Area)\nHead to the path on the left to find a hot air balloon ride. Use the grappling points afterwards to find a magic rope leading down to a Pictos.

Name: Energising Rush
LongDescription: Endless Tower\nComplete Stage 2, Trial 3

Name: Charging Critical
Description: +20% Gradient Charge on Critical Hit. Once per turn
LongDescription: Endless Tower\nComplete Stage 5, Trial 3

Name: Critical Weakness
LongDescription: Endless Tower\nComplete Stage 6, Trial 3

Name: Rush on Powerful
LongDescription: Endless Tower\nComplete Stage 9, Trial 3

Name: Greater Powerless
LongDescription: Endless Tower\nComplete Stage 10, Trial 3

Name: Anti-Burn
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nFrom the Flag, run towards the faded boy to find a staircase past him. Take it down to find a magic rope that leads to an elevator. Fight the giant rock monster (Gargant)

Name: Charging Alteration
Description: +10% of a Gradient Charge on applying a buff. Once per turn.
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nFrom the Flag, run towards the faded boy to find a staircase past him. Take it down to find a magic rope that leads to an elevator and a new area. Run down the stairs, head towards the left to find a grapple point. Follow the path and grapple to reach the Pictos.

Name: Energetic Healer
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nThe Picto can be found on the ledge to the left after riding the rope up in the lower section of Flying Manor.

Name: Painter
Description: Convert all Physical damage to Void damage
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nFrom the Flag, go towards the grapple point leading to the big locked door. Look to the right to find a large picture frame you can walk on. It'll lead to a new area. You'll find this Picto on one of the upper walkways.

Name: Powerful Revive
Description: Apply Powerful for three turns when Revived
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nBeat the Dualliste and then go to the upper area near where you fought him to find a grapple point leading to a Paint Cage containing the Pictos.

Name: Empowering Break
Description: Gain Powerful on Breaking a target
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nTake the elevator right next to the Flag. When you get up, follow the path and hug the left to find a magic rope. Stay on the left and find a grapple that leads to the Pictos behind a monster

Name: Accelerating Shots
Description: 20% chance to gain Rush on Free Aim shot
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nTake the elevator right next to the Flag. When you get up, follow the path and then once it splits into three, head on the left path to find a merchant.

Name: Gradient Breaker
Description: 50% increased Break damage when using Gradient attacks
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\n(1) Take the elevator right next to the Flag. When you get up, follow the path and then once it splits into three, head on the left path to find a merchant. (2) You can find the Gradient Break Pictos in a small cave along one of the paths behind the Grandis NPC at Endless Night Sanctuary.

Name: Break Specialist
Description: Break damage is increased by 50%, but base damage is reduced by 20%
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nTake the elevator right next to the Flag. When you get up, follow the path and then once it splits into three, head on the left path to find a merchant.

Name: Slowing Break
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nTake the elevator right next to the Flag. When you get up, follow the path and then once it splits into three, head on the left path to find a merchant.

Name: Energising Shots
Description: 20% chance to gain 1 AP on Free Aim shot
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nDefeat Goblu as part of the challenge (take the elevator next to the flag). The Pictos will be next to Goblu.

Name: Clea's Life
Description: On turn start, if no damage taken since last turn, recover 100% health
LongDescription: Flying Manor - Central Plaza\nDefeat Clea at the end of Flying Manor.

Name: SOS Rush
Description: Apply Rush when falling below 50% Health.
LongDescription: Falling Leaves - Resinveil Groove\nFrom Journal 35, turn around and walk along the stone path. Look to the right for the Pictos.

Name: Beneficial Contamination
Description: +2 AP on applying a Status Effect. Once per turn.
LongDescription: Falling Leaves - Resinveil Groove\nLeft from the flag, grapple across and follow the path to a Merchant.

Name: Greater Slow
LongDescription: Sky Island - Entrance\nFind a staircase at the end of this small map.

Name: In Medias Res
Description: +3 Shields on Battle Start, but max health is halved
LongDescription: Dark Shores - Bloodied Beach\nRun straight past the flag to the end of the area to find this surrounded by enemies.

Name: Energising Revive
Description: +3 AP to all Allies when revived
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs Cave\nBeat the Chromatic Hexga at the end.

Name: Exhausting Power
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs Cave\nBeat the Chromatic Hexga at the end. Look to the left of it.

Name: Solidifying
Description: +2 Shields when the character's Health falls below 50%. Once per battle.
LongDescription: Sacred River\nBuy from Merchant for 67,350 Chroma.

Name: Critical Stun
Description: 100% on Critical Chance on hitting a Stunned target
LongDescription: Sacred River\nBuy from Merchant for 53,880 Chroma.

Name: First Offensive
Description: First hit dealt and taken deals 50% more damage.
LongDescription: Abbest Cave\nBeat Chromatic Abbest

Name: Energising Attack I
LongDescription: Painting Workshop\nSolve the Painting Workshop mystery and defeat the Lampmaster

Name: The One
LongDescription: Sunless Cliffs\nBeat the Mime at the Portal.

Name: Base Shield
Description: +1 Shield if not affected by any Shield on turn start
LongDescription: The Chosen Path\nDefeat the mirror challenges and enter the double doors up the staircase.

Name: Pro Retreat
LongDescription: Camp\nFind all nine Lost Gestrals for Sastro

Name: Burning Break
Description: Apply 3 burn stacks on Breaking a target
LongDescription: Frozen Hearts - Glacial Falls\nIf you're facing the bells near the flag, turn right and hug the wall. Run up the cliff, and then you'll see the Pictos across the way that you can jump to by using a frozen bell.

Name: Burn Affinity
LongDescription: Frozen Hearts - Glacial Falls\nFrom the Flag, look out towards the flaming enemies to see a magic rope. Take it up to find an area with some Chroma. Follow the path up there to find a grappling hook. Use the handholds and then jump to a path on the right to find another grapple point leading to the Pictos.

Name: Death Bomb
Description: On Death, deal damage to all enemies.
LongDescription: Yellow Harvest - Harvester's Hollow\nPass the flag and head to the right of the tall stone statue. There is a short path to the right of the long ramp, and the Pictos is at the end.

Name: Auto Death
LongDescription: Yellow Harvest (Harvester's Hollow)\nBuy from nearby Merchant for 5320 Chroma. From the flag, head towards the right to find a slope that leads to an area with blue lamps. You'll find a grapple point.

Name: Teamwork
Description: 10% increased damage while all allies are alive
LongDescription: Yellow Harvest (Harvester's Hollow)\nFrom the flag, go straight into the large clearing. Stay on the right until you find a large slope that leads to an area with lamps. Use the grapple point at the end to find a Merchant.

Name: Quick Break
Description: Play again after Breaking a target
LongDescription: Renoir's Drafts - Entrance\nHook a left after passing the flag to find a grapple point.

Name: Aegis Revival
LongDescription: Renoir's Drafts - Entrance\nFollow the main path until you reach the fading man. Walk down the slope on the right once you pass him. Hook a left before entering the round gate to find a slope that leads to a grapple point and a Merchant.

Name: Charging Burn
Description: +20% of a Gradient Charge on applying Burn. Once per turn.
LongDescription: Renoir's Drafts - Entrance\nFollow the main path until you reach the fading man. Walk down the slope on the right once you pass him. Hook a left before entering the round gate to find a slope that leads to a grapple point and a Merchant. Jump on the bridge behind the Merchant.

Name: Recovery
LongDescription: Red Woods\nDonate Chroma to help Benisseur.

Name: Combo Attack III
LongDescription: Dark Gestral Arena\nComplete the Dark Gestral Arena

Name: Auto Powerful
Description: Apply Powerful for 3 turns on battle start
LongDescription: Floating Cemetery\nFight the Chalier.

Name: Survivor
Description: Survive fatal damage with 1 Health. Once per battle.
LongDescription: Monoco's Station\nDeliver the Eternal Ice to the Grandis Trader nearby.

Name: Greater Rush
LongDescription: Monoco's Station\nThe Greater Rush Pictos is purchasable from the Grandis merchant in Monoco's Station for 85,750 Chroma after retrieving the Eternal Ice from the Gargant in Frozen Hearts.

Name: Shielding Death
Description: On death, allies gain 3 Shield points.
LongDescription: The Crows\nBeat the Chromatic Chapelier at The Crows (shoot all the crows)

Name: Powerful Shield
Description: 10% Increased damage per Shield Point on self.
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nPurchase from the Merchant.

Name: Powerful Heal
Description: Healing an ally also applies Powerful for 1 turn.
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nPurchase from the Merchant.

Name: Protecting Attack
Description: Gain Shell for 1 turn on Base Attack
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nPurchase from the Merchant.

Name: Charging Mark
Description: +20% of a Gradient Charge on hitting a Marked target. Once per turn
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nPurchase from the Merchant.

Name: Accelerating Tint
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nPurchase from the Merchant.

Name: Shell On Rush
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nPurchase from the Merchant.

Name: Anti-Freeze
LongDescription: Frozen Hearts\nCan be obtained upon destroying the Paint Cage in Glacial Falls past the Manor entrance.

Name: Critical Break
Description: 25% increased Break damage on Critical Hits.
LongDescription: The Continent\nYou can find the Pictos by destroying a Paint Spike on a beach northeast of The Reacher.

Name: Critical Vulnerability
Description: 25% increased Critical Chance on Defenceless enemies.
LongDescription: The Continent\nYou can find the Pictos surrounded by Nevrons in an abandoned camp northwest of the Floating Cemetary.

Name: Effective Support
LongDescription: The Continent\nYou can find Effective Support Pictos surrounded by Nevrons northeast of Sirene.

Name: Energising Burn
Description: +1 AP on applying Burn. Once per turn.
LongDescription: Frozen Hearts\nEnergising Burn is obtained as a drop by defeating Chromatic Veilleur found at Frozen Hearts.

Name: Energising Stun
Description: +1 AP on hitting a Stunned target with a Skill.
LongDescription: Flying Manor\nEnergising Stun is obtained as a reward for solving a Painted Cage puzzle in the Flying Manor area.

Name: Marking Break
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nPurchase from the Merchant.

Name: Powerful Mark
Description: Gain Powerful on hitting a Marked enemy.
LongDescription: Flying Manor\nYou can find the Powerful Mark Pictos being guarded by two Steel Chevalieres on a platform in the Goblu boss area.

Name: Powerful Shots
Description: 20% chance to gain Powerful on Free Aim shot.
LongDescription: Gestral Village\nYou can find the Powerful Shots Pictos by breaking a Paint Spike near the Gestral doctor.

Name: Rejuvenating Revive
Description: Apply Regen for 3 turns when revived.
LongDescription: Stone Wave Cliffs\nYou can get the Rejuvenating Revive Pictos after breaking a Paint Spike in the Old Farm area.

Name: Shielding Tint
LongDescription: The Continent\nThis can be found on the ground under wooden crates near the Bourgeon southeast of Forgotten Battlefield (requires Esquie flight).

Name: Protecting Shots
Description: 20% chance to gain Shell on Free Aim shot.
LongDescription:
Flying Manor\nAfter entering the Flying Manor, go down the first flight of stairs facing the Nevron statue, then turn right and jump off the staircase leading to a cliff.
Go down the rope and continue walking to the right. You'll find the Pictos sitting on the edge of a broken picture frame.

Name: Gradient Break
LongDescription: Endless Night Sanctuary\nThe Gradient Break Pictos can be found in a tiny alcove in the passage between the two paths past the behind the Grandis Engineer in Endless Night Sanctuary.

Name: Fracture Survivor
Description: Old Lumiere\nFrom the Left Street, make your way down the path through the broken doorway then continue to the second open field. Take the path on the right and drop down inside the large broken pipe, use the Old Key on the gate and pick up the journal

Name: Expedition 34
Description: The Crows\nFound to the right of the Entrance

Name: Expedition 35
Description: Falling Leaves\nFound next to the bridge leading to the Chromatic Ballet within the Resinveil Grove

Name: Expedition 36
Description: White Tree\nFound to the right at the base of the tree upon entering White Tree

Name: Expedition 37
Description: Gestral Beach\nLocated east to The Sunless Cliffs, requieres Esquie's ability to fly

Name: Expedition 38
Description: Yellow Harvest\nFound by a few corpses surrounded by lit lamps on a cliffside to the right of the Harverster's Hollow section

Name: Expedition 39
Description: Visages\nIn the Sadness Vale area, after picking up the Energy Tint Shard, head to the other path and climb up the ledge

Name: Expedition 40
Description: The Continent\nExit Sirene and swim toward The Monolith, pick up the Journal in the upper left corner of the isle, next to the Merchant Granasori

Name: Expedition 41
Description: Forgotten Battlefield\nIn the Battlefield section, go to the trenches on the right side of the Fading Woman. On the left side, you can find a small area containing the journal

Name: Expedition 42
Description: Old Lumiere\nFrom the Manor Gardens, head to the upper right corner to find a new path. Follow it and take the rope down, pick up journal at the end of the path

Name: Expedition 43
Description: The Continent\nFound in an abandoned expedition camp, on an island northeast of the Coastal Cave

Name: Expedition 44
Description: Yellow Harvest\nFrom the Harvester's Hollow, continue ahead towards the path on the left. Past the slope on the right, you will find a corpse holding a lit lamp on the left with the Journal

Name: Expedition 45
Description: Crushing Cavern\nAfter defeating the Giant Sapling, head into the tunnel ahead until you reach the fork path. Take the left path and pick up Journal

Name: Expedition 46
Description: Sirene's Dress\nFound by some rubble across the arena where you fight the Chromatic Glissando

Name: Expedition 47
Description: The Continent\nFound beside a collapsed structure, near the merchant Carnovi

Name: Expedition 49
Description: Falling Leaves\nComplete the Fading Spirit Quest to open the gate, continue up the path and make your way up to the cliff to find the journal by a set of broken stairs.

Name: Expedition 50
Description: Stone Wave Cliffs\nFrom the Paintress Shrine, head down the path on the right and cross the bridge. Take the path on the left and pick up the journal

Name: Expedition 51
Description: Frozen Hearts\nFrom the Icebound Train Station, cross the tracks and make your way up the hill. Once you reach the top where you see the end of a train, turn right into a crack in the wall to find journal

Name: Expedition 52
Description: Gestral Village\nFound on a narrow path near the Gestral Doctor

Name: Expedition 53
Description: The Small Bourgeon\nFound at the end of the path to the left of the Bourgeon

Name: Expedition 54
Description: Stone Wave Cliffs Cave\nFound on the right side of the Arena, where you fight the Chromatic Hexga

Name: Expedition 55
Description: Sirene\nFrom the Dancing Classes, continue down the path and up the stairs to the plaza filled with enemies. To the right, you can find the journal

Name: Expedition 56
Description: Stone Wave Cliffs\nFrom the Entrance, head down the path and through the broken airship, use your grappling hook to reach the other side. Head down the path and head down on the left path. Take out the enemy and pick up the journal at the base of the statue

Name: Expedition 57
Description: Forgotten Battlefield\nIn the Battlefield section, you can find an open area after passing through the Paint Cage. In the middle of the field, you can find the journal

Name: Expedition 58
Description: Old Lumiere\nFound within a cutscene when playing as Lune, Sciel, and Monoco past the Left Street

Name: Expedition 59
Description: Yellow Harvest\nFrom the Yellow Spire Wrecks, head left into a cave to find the journal by the structure in the middle

Name: Expedition 60
Description: Lumiere\nFound if you interact with the ledge on the right outside the opera house. Ask Esquie to bring an item to the surface, and you will obtain the journal

Name: Expedition 61
Description: The Reacher\nFrom the Foggy Area, cross the bridge and go straight ahead to the lit areas on the upper portion of the field. Proceed through the cave to find journal

Name: Expedition 62
Description: The Continent\nFound at a camp to the left of the beach behind Gestral Village

Name: Expedition 63
Description: Ancient Sanctuary\nFound by a fork in the path in the Sanctuary Maze section near a Paint Cage

Name: Expedition 64
Description: The Continent\nFound on a camp along the path to the left of the entrance to The Meadows, you will need Esquie's swim ability to reach this area

Name: Expedition 65
Description: Monoco's Station\nAfter defeating the Stalact, head into the station past Monoco's Station flag. Cross the tracks at the end of the path and turn left to find the journal

Name: Expedition 66
Description: Esquie's Nest\nFound at a camp on the fork of the path after Esquie joins your party

Name: Expedition 67
Description: Sirene\nFound by a pile of boxes after being transported past the Crumbling Path flag

Name: Expedition 68
Description: Flying Waters\nGo through the main path in the Coral Cave, you can find the journal lying on the ground at the path with lanterns at the beginning

Name: Expedition 69
Description: Visages\nIn the Joyful Vale section, you can find the journal behind enemies on the left path

Name: Expedition 70
Description: The Monolith\nFrom the Tainted Lumiere, head down to the main square and follow the path behind the statue. Grapple across the next area and continue making your way through the broken streets. At the fork of the road, head straight and go behind the flower stalls on the right. Take the right turn, grapple across through the floating islands, take out the enemies and get behind the building to pick up the journal

Name: Expedition 78
Description: Stone Wave Cliffs\nFrom the Entrance, head down the path and take the top up on the right. Once you reach the top, you can find the journal on the right

Name: Expedition 81
Description: Spring Meadows\nPicked up during a cutscene when Lune and Gustave find Jar for the first time

Name: Expedition 84
Description: The Fountain\nRequires Esquie's fly ability to reach the location. Can be found on the path to the right of the fountain

Name: Julie Search and Rescue
Description: The Continent\nFound beside a collapsed tent, west of the Forgotten Battlefield. To reach this area, you’ll need to progress the story far enough to Fly

Name: Simon
Description: The Abyss\nFound in the middle of the area after defeating Simon

Name: Aline
Description: The Manor\nEnter The Manor from the entrance in the Tainted Battlefield in The Monolith to reach the Garden, the journal can be found by the statue in the center

Name: Renoir
Description: The Manor\nEnter The Manor from the entrance in Old Lumiere, and exit the bathroom to a bedroom. The Journal can be found on the nightstand

Name: Unkown 1
Description: The Manor\nFound inside a bedroom in The Manor, which can be accessed from the Visages

Name: Unkown 2
Description: The Manor\nFound inside a room in The Manor, which can be accessed from The Reacher

Name: Unkown 3
Description: The Manor\nPlace the Manor Family Canvas quest item on the empty frame in The Manor to unlock the Painting Room. There's an empty frame just by the stairs on the east wing of the manor, near the flag

Name: Verso
Description: The Continent\nLocated just by the foot of a destroyed building west to Stone Quarry. Requires Esquie's swim ability and destroy coral reefs to reach it, or his Fly ability

Name: Maelle - Skirt
LongDescription:
From the Tide Caverns Expedition Flag, get across to the next cliff and follow the lanterns. Take the 
rope down and head to the right side of the cave past the Rocher Boss. Take the rope down and 
defeat the Gold Chevaliere. Enter the doors ahead to enter The Manor and open the wardrobe

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: In front of Esquie's Nest

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: As you approach the entrance to the Stone Wave Cliffs, they will see a path to their right that leads to a Bourgeon. There is a Lost Gestral in an alcove just beyond that enemy.

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: There is a Lost Gestral just southeast of Monoco's Station, in the northeast of the area

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: After unlocking the ability to swim, this Lost gestral can be found on the same island as White Tree, west of Yellow Harvest. The Gestral is on the south side of the island

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: After unlocking the ability to swim through coral reefs, you can find this Lost Gestral on the beach above Coastal Cave

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: There is a red island northwest of Old Lumiere. The gestal is hidden in the corner next to two Mimes. Swim is required for this one, but in order to reach this area of the map that should already be unlocked

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: After unlocking the ability to Fly, head towards the endless tower. There is a single rock platform high in the air by the tower, and a Lost Gestral stands upon it.

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: After unlocking the ability to Fly, head toward the left side of Visages or northeast of the Reacher. Esquie can land on some land in that area and the Lost Gestral is standing near its south end

Name: Lost Gestral
LongDescription: After unlocking the ability to Fly, this Lost Gestral can be found in the red area southwest of Sirene, near the portal to the Endless Night Sanctuary

Name: Alicia
LongDescription: Enter the Manor door through the Falling Leaves location to transport yourself to Alicia's study. The Manor door can be found in the lower area of the Falling Leaves, in the cavern where the Lady of Sap is

Name: Alicia's Birthday Party
LongDescription: Requires Esquie to acquire a new ability that can destroy the coral reefs

Name: Aline
LongDescription: Found at the dead end of this location, next to a rowboat. Requires Esquie's fly ability to reach the location

Name: Aline's Glasshouse
LongDescription: Clear out the Yellow Harvest location to reach the other exit where you can find the entrance to the Lost Woods.

Name: Children of Lumiere
LongDescription: Can be purchased from Citrelo for 1000 Chroma. Requires Esquie's fly ability to reach the location

Name: Clea
LongDescription: Complete all 11 Stages which is a total of 33 challenges. Requires Esquie's Fly ability to reach the entrance of the location

Name: Clea! Don't Pull Your Sister's Hair!
LongDescription: The entrance for this room is located in Frozen Hearts

Name: Endless Light
LongDescription: Requires Esquie's swim underwater ability to reach the location. From the Entrance Expedition Flag, head down the path and take the path directly to the left of the slope you came from. Grapple to the building, head down the path and pick up the Music Record on the right side of the field

Name: Forlorn
LongDescription: Requires Esquie's fly ability to reach the entrance from The Continent. It is east to The Meadows, before the Chromatic Benisseur

Name: Goblu
LongDescription: Purchased from the Gestral Merchant Blabary for 1000 Chroma

Name: Gustave
LongDescription: Return to the area where you fought the main boss and where the cutscene took place. You'll find it in the ground by the edge of the cliff

Name: Honeymoon in Lumiere
LongDescription: Progress the story to acquire the swim ability for Esquie and to reach the location

Name: L'Amour D'Une Mère
LongDescription: Enter the Manor through The Monolith entrance from the Tainted Battledfields, it can be found to the left upon entering

Name: Le Grand Cafe de Lumiere
LongDescription: As you approach the Carousel from the Expedition flag, take a path to the left. The record is at the end

Name: Lettre à Maelle (Missable)
LongDescription: Progress the story in Act II. After defeating an axon, in the Camp. Choose "Check up on the others". You'll acquire this record after the cutscene

Name: Lights of the Past
LongDescription: Requires Esquie to destroy the rock obstacles blocking the path to the location

Name: Linen and Cotton
LongDescription: Can be purchased from Rubiju for 1000 Chroma

Name: Lost Voice
LongDescription: Can be purchased from Strabami for 5000 Chroma

Name: Lumiere
LongDescription:
Acquired as a drop by defeating the Mime enemy located in Lumiere during the Prologue section of the game.
Or, if you missed it, buy it from the merchant near the entrance to the Isle of the Eyes.

Name: Lune
LongDescription: Reach Relationship Level 6 with Lune and complete her side quest

Name: Monoco
LongDescription: Reach Relationship Level 6 with Monoco and complete his side quest

Name: Nocturne Pour Lumiere
LongDescription: Found next to the remains of an expedition. Climb to the top section of the cave, and then go east to find an opening on the ground that you can jump to drop onto a platform where the dead expeditioner and the music record is

Name: Nocturne Pour Un Masque De Tristesse
LongDescription: Trigger the four switches in the dining room, and then investigate the fireplace to find this music record

Name: Our Drafts Collide
LongDescription: Automatically unlocked and added to the list of music records upon defeating the final boss of the main campaign in Act III

Name: Our Painted Family
LongDescription: Progress the story to acquire the swim ability for Esquie and to reach the location

Name: Renoir
LongDescription: Enter The Manor from Old Lumiere, and pick up the record on the sink directly to the right upon entering

Name: Reverence
LongDescription: Progress the story to acquire the swim ability for Esquie and to reach the location

Name: Rêveries Dans Paris
LongDescription: Can be found on the right side behind the casino

Name: Robe de Jour
LongDescription: Can be purchased from Rederi for 1000 Chroma

Name: Sciel
LongDescription: Reach Relationship Level 6 with Sciel. Progress the story around Act III and choose to spend time with her back at camp

Name: Un 33 Decembre a Lumiere
LongDescription: Requires Esquie to destroy the rock obstacles blocking the path to the location

Name: Until Next Life
LongDescription: Defeat the Scavenger boss and return to the Young Boy. Speak to him to acquire this record

Name: Verso
LongDescription: Access The Manor through the door inside a cavern in the Anger Vale section of Visages. In the room, the record is besides the baby grand piano

Name: Ancient Sanctuary
Description: Near the expedition flag at the entrance, chase the Petank across the log bridge to the glowing plate on the other side of the stream

Name: Esquie's Nest
Description: From the entrance, go through the narrow tunnel and drop down from the left side of the bridge, approach from the left so the Petank runs through the cave on the right, the glowing plate is between two large rocks at the end

Name: Stone Wave Cliffs
Description: At the Old Farm checkpoint, look for the Petank beneath the first cabin on the right, approach from behind and guide it through the gates into a narrow alley where the glowing plate is located

Name: Endless Night Sanctuary
Description: From the Night Totem flag, head toward the exit past the Ultimate Sakapatate, instead of leaving, keep to the left to find a tunnel leading to a new area, follow the path to the Petank and guide it to the glowing plate

Name: Frozen Hearts
Description: Located to the left of an abandoned building next to a piano, before the expedition flag at Frozen Heart, chase the Petank northward until it reaches the glowing plate

Name: Forgotten Battlefield
Description: From the Battlefield flag, move through the main area until you find the purple Petank, approach it from the right so it flees to its left, then circle around and approach from the 3 o’clock direction (as if coming from the right side of the map) to push it toward the far end of the area. Finally, approach from its left to guide it directly onto the glowing plate

Name: The Reacher
Description: In the same area with one of the Mansion’s doors, descend the spiral ramp to a lower floor, chase the Petank toward the cliff’s edge, clearing out the Nevrons along the way

Name: Isle of Eyes
Description: Climb the stairs and go under a mannequin with an eye on its chest, jump from the right side of the platform to drop into the area with the Petank. Guide it around the stone pillars to the glowing plate next to another mannequin

Name: Sirene
Description: After using a floating disc to reach a room with a large statue, enter the room behind the statue to find the red Petank. Approach from the left to make it run into the statue room, then into the room on the right where it can be cornered

Name: Sirene
Description: Located to the left of the Glissando boss area. Look among the floating rubble of one of the broken columns for handholds. After crossing, drop a light rope to reach the lower level with the Petank. Chase it until it stops at the base of the stairs, then guide it onto the glowing plate

Name: The Monolith
Description: From the Tainted Cliffs checkpoint, ascend the spiral staircase. Continue along the path until you reach a group of Cultists. The glowing green plate is located next to them. The Petank can be found in the open area beyond the Cultists

Name: The Continent
Description: A Chromatic Petank can be found on the overworld. To find it, head east from the central map area and look for a glowing chromatic aura in the distance. The Petank will appear with a colorful, radiant glow, making it easy to spot. To capture it, approach carefully without startling it. Follow the Petank as it moves through the area, and eventually, it will stop at a glowing circle

Name: Flying Manor
Description: In the path to the Eveques bossfight, in the back corner, there should be a canvas near a ramp, the Petank should be visible from there

Name: Gustave/Verso - Cruleram
Description: Flying Waters, Coastal Cave, Flying Manor, Endless Night Sanctuary

Name: Gustave/Verso - Gaulteram
Description: The Continent, Yellow Harvest, Lumiere (Act III)

Name: Gustave/Verso - Lanceram
Description: Spring Meadows, Coastal Cave, Flying Manor

Name: Gustave/Verso - Sakaram
Description: Ancient Sanctuary, Gestral Village, Dark Gestral Arena

Name: Lune - Lighterim
Description: Spring Meadows, Coastal Cave, Flying Manor

Name: Lune - Trebuchim
Description: Ancient Sanctuary, Gestral Village, Dark Gestral Arena

Name: Lune - Troubadim
Description: Flying Waters, Flying Manor, Forgotten Battlefield

Name: Sciel - Chation
Description: Stone Wave Cliffs, Flying Manor, The Continent, The Monolith

Name: Monoco - Ballaro
Description: The Continent, Lumiere (Act III), Sirene's Dress

Name: Flush Surface
Description: Own the SwirlForce surface cleaner and all of its attachments at once. The SwirlForce is fairly cheap and amazing for cleaning floors and low walls, so it should be an early purchase.

Name: Leading Light
Description: Own any Light Duty washer and all of its attachments at once. The Prime Vista 1500 is the cheapest option for this.

Name: Happy Medium
Description: Own any Medium Duty washer and all of its attachments at once. The Prime Vista 2400 is the cheapest option for this.

Name: Heavy Water
Description: Own any Heavy Duty washer and all of its attachments at once. The Prime Vista 3000 is the cheapest option for this.

Name: Consummate Professional
Description: Own any Professional Duty washer and all of its attachments at once. The Prime Vista Pro is the cheapest option for this.

Name: Maxed Out
Description: Own all washers and attachments simultaneously. You'll need to complete the game, then buy everything that you still don't have.

Name: Staying Adaptable
Description: Complete any job using only the Adaptable Nozzle. This means you can't use soap; pick a quick, early job like the Removals Van with a Medium- or higher level washer.

Name: Three-Pronged Approach
Description: Complete any job using only the Prime Vista Triple-Tip Nozzle. The Triple-Tip is only available on the Prime Vista Pro. Small vehicles like the Dog Car are a good choice to quickly unlock this award once you have the necessary equipment.

Name: Double Top
Description: Complete any job using only the UrbanX Double Turbo Nozzle The Double Turbo is only available on the UrbanX Stream. The Mobility Scooter is a small vehicle whose many crevasses are perfect for the Double Turbo.

Name: Purr Bonding
Description: Pet all three cats in the Home Base

Name: Gnome From Home
Description: Pick up the hidden Gnome in the Home Base. He's hiding behind the door at the top of the stairs.

Name: Taking Note
Description: Examine any note on the bulletin board.

Name: Geo-Cashing
Description: Select a job from the map in the office.

Name: Home Decor
Description: Buy, clean, and place a piece of furniture.

Name: Dressed For Success
Description: Buy and equip any outfit cosmetic.

Name: Radical Rebrand
Description: Buy and equip a van skin.

Name: Washing In Style
Description: Buy and equip a washer skin. These don't become available until late in the game, and then only for the highest-tier, Professional Duty washers.

Name: All Moved In
Description: Removals Van. Complete the first Career job.

Name: Hit The Lights
Description: Campsite. Using only the red (smallest) setting on the basic nozzle, clean all the lanterns before cleaning anything else. The lanterns are near the chair by the cabin, at the far end of the stepping stones, on the fire pit ring, and next to the telescope. The hanging lantern over the door does not count, so don't clean it until the other four are finished.

Name: High Pressure
Description: Billboard. Complete any task while abseiling.

Name: Doggy Bath
Description: Dog Car. Have soap on every cleanable part of the car simultaneously.

Name: Tea Time
Description: Teapot Tea Room. Find all six Gnomes and place one in each seat around the tables out front.

Name: Rise And Shine
Description: Teapot Tea Room. Place a Gnome on the Scissor Lift, then raise it all the way up.

Name: Where's Woolly?
Description: Shooting Gallery. Clean the Bigfoot Target before cleaning anything else.

Name: Drop The Ball
Description: Gas Station. Roll the soccer ball down the playground slide.

Name: Floor Is Lava
Description: Stone Circle. Stand on all six Pillars without touching the floor in between any of them.

Name: Flying Start
Description: Rock Climbing Park. Clean the Pterodactyl first.

Name: Make It All Shine
Description: Roller Disco. Clean the Disco Ball before cleaning anything else.

Name: Deep Lore
Description: Temple Interior. Enter the hidden room.

Name: Message Received
Description: Car And Trailer. Clean the Satellite Dish before cleaning anything else.

Name: Door To Door
Description: Motel. Clean all six doors, including their numbers and handles, before cleaning anything else.

Name: Front Row Seats
Description: Theater. Clean the front row of seats entirely before cleaning anything else.

Name: Ticket To Ride
Description: Mini Roller Coaster. Ride the roller coaster from start to finish.

Name: Cosmic Ordering
Description: Solar System Exhibit. Clean the Sun, then all the planets in order.

Name: Spin Doctor
Description: Fun House. Clean any Rotating Floor Disc using the SwirlForce surface cleaner.

Name: Glissando!
Description: Fun House. Hit all the keys on the giant piano in order from left to right.

Name: Wise Decision
Description: Shopping Mall. Clean the Owl Statue before cleaning anything else.

Name: Squeaky Clean
Description: Town Floats. Clean the Country Mouse last.

Name: It All Comes Out In The Wash
Description: Mount Rushless. Complete every job in Career Mode.

Name: Give and Gather Sweater Outfit - Badtz-maru

Alternating Critical
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. On Critical hit, 100% increased damage of the next non-Critical hit. Across from Mime in Verso's Drafts

Name: AP Discount
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Skills cost 1 less AP. Purchased from Najabla merchant in Verso's Drafts

Name: Clea's Death
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Upon death, allies gain +25% damage until they die. Defeat Clea Unleashed in Endless Tower

Name: Consuming Attack
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Base attack consumes up to 100 Burns to deal 10% more damage per Burn consumed. Purchased from Najabla merchant in Verso's Drafts

Name: Damage Share
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. 50% damage taken is redirected to other allies (if possible). Defeat the two "Francois-type" enemies near the #8 Marelle (hopscotch) piece by the Reverie Path rest point in Verso's Drafts.

Name: Double Third
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Every third hit of a Skill deals double damage. Defeat Barbasucette enemies in Verso's Drafts

Name: Empowering Jumps
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Counters deal 100% more damage for each successful Jump Counter this turn. Complete Gestral see-saw challenge

Name: Empowered Healer
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Using a Healing Skill gives 50% more damage for 1 turn. Parkour across some broken platforms near the Reverie Path rest point in Verso's Drafts

Name: Feint
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Start each turn with 4 Barpapa stacks. Every 5th hit with a Skill deals 600% more damage. Counter Monsieur Frappe's attacks near the carousel swings

Name: First Life
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. 25% increased damage until death. 20% decreased damage on death. (Once) Interact with new painting and defeat Chromatic Lampmaster

Name: Frenzy
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Each successful Skill hit deals 10% more damage. Defeat Licornapieds at Licornapieds' Station In Verso's Drafts after opening the gingerbread door to the birthday party (requires collecting Cake Pieces)

Name: Gradient Overcharge
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. On turn start, consume 3 Gradient Charges (if able) to deal 200% more damage this turn. On a lollipop platform during the parkour course up to the Chromatic Licorne.

Name: Gradient Parry
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. +5% of a gradient charge on Parry. When solving the scattered Marelle puzzle, go up the hill to find it near the #5 piece.

Name: Longer Break
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Breaks last 1 more turn, but the target can't be Broken twice. Defeat wheel-type enemies near pink paint cage by Gestral Baths rest point.

Name: Slowing Attack
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Base attack applies Slow for 1 turn. Found in a waterfall in the Gestral Resort

Name: SOS Healing Tint
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Consume a Healing Tint when falling below 50% Health. Defeat enemies near Gingerbread door

Name: Trigger Happy
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. After shooting 10 times in the same turn, gain +2 AP (once). And following Shots this turn deal 200% more damage. Pop the balloons and duel the Half-baked Gestral (shoot his balloons during battle)

Name: Chromatic Barbasucette
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Verso's Drafts.

Name: Chromatic Franctale
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Verso's Drafts.

Name: Chromatic Machinapieds
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Verso's Drafts.

Name: Half-Baked Gestral
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Verso's Drafts.

Name: Licornapieds
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Verso's Drafts.

Name: Osquio
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Verso's Drafts.

Name: Chromatic Lampmaster
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Endless Tower

Name: Clea Unleashed
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Endless Tower

Name: Duollistes
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Endless Tower

Name: Simon The Divergent Star
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Location: Endless Tower

Name: Baguettaro
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Acquired as a reward for defeating the Mime near the Candy Land Expedition Flag.

Name: Bonbim
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Sold by the Gestral Merchant Najabla for 102,424 Chroma.

Name: Cleim
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Acquired as a reward for defeating Clea Unleashed.

Name: Duollison
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Acquired as a reward for defeating the Duollistes.

Name: Esqium
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. 	Head west from the Reverie Path Expedition Flag and go down the grappling point.

Name: Esquiaro
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. At the Gestral Baths, attack the Nevron blocking the way on the diving board, and this will allow you to pick up the item at the far end.

Name: Esquim
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Solve the Painted Cage Puzzle after the Open Playground Expedition Flag.

Name: Esquion
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Solve the Painted Cage Puzzle after the Open Playground Expedition Flag.

Name: Esquiso
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Acquired as a reward for defeating Osquio.

Name: Licorum
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Defeat the Chromatic Licorne

Name: Sucreso
Description: Verso's Draft DLC. Located behind the grand piano on the tree house balcony, north from the talking door.
